From c7d136da0763a7f5800ce91825f15309e7f5f155 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: sarabjeets <sarabjeets@marvell.com>
Date: Mon, 19 Jan 2026 10:06:48 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] Change orchagent BFD creation from CFG_DB to APP_DB

As part of sonic-bfd.yang, we have created a new table BFD_PEER (which
was already being unofficially used in frrcfgd.py).

Here we are enabling orchagent code to utilize this new table instead of
BFD table in APP_DB. This allows us to reach persistency of data across
reboots/reloads.

As per the current design, we are maintaining bfd such that either only
HW offload BFD or Software BFD will be supported.
This will be based on bfd_data_plane_mode flag.

Signed-off-by: sarabjeets <sarabjeets@marvell.com>
